                            <comment id="17722184" author="thomas.woeckinger" created="Fri, 12 May 2023 13:45:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=houston&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;houston&quot;&gt;houston&lt;/a&gt; as you introduced the, you may take this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is really hard to write a unit test for this, as you need at least a servlert container with JSF.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The changes are in CoreContainer line 754 and 755.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17722214" author="houston" created="Fri, 12 May 2023 15:34:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is your idea to save the previous thread context classLoader before the solrClassloader is used, and then reset it at the end of the load method?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17722698" author="thomas.woeckinger" created="Mon, 15 May 2023 08:29:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, this was my intention, i will provide a pull request today.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think a better solution is avoiding the set of context class loader, but I&apos;m not sure if this is possible with regard of loading the kerberos plugin.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17723105" author="thomas.woeckinger" created="Tue, 16 May 2023 12:03:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reduced the scope of the context class loader to load auth plugins only.&lt;/p&gt;

